      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Mideast Peace, Derailed Again</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Elihu Ben Klein letter blames Ariel Sharon and extremist allies for undermining Mideast peace process</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your strong criticism of Ariel Sharon, the Likud leader (editorial, Oct. 3), goes to the heart of the cause of the current outbreak of violence in the Middle East.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your strong criticism of Ariel Sharon, the Likud leader (editorial, Oct. 3), goes to the heart of the cause of the current outbreak of violence in the Middle East.</p>
        <p>I am a Jew, yet I blame Mr. Sharon and his extremist supporters for undermining the peace process. The former general is transparent in his desire to undermine Prime Minister Ehud Barak politically. In this latest episode of bloodshed, I completely sympathize with the Palestinians.</p>
        <p>ELIHU BEN KLEIN  Westport, Conn., Oct. 3, 2000</p>
      </block>
